name: West Papuan Lorikeet
rangeDescription: Western new guinea (montane forest of bird's head peninsula)
description: A large, very long-tailed lorikeet of mid and upper montane forest. Has a red head and chest, yellow on the side of the chest and lower flanks, green wings, dark patch on the belly, and green base to the tail and yellow tail tip.

name: Whistling Kite
rangeDescription: Australia, new guinea, and new caledonia
description: Large sandy-colored raptor. In flight it has a strong underwing pattern, and holds its wings in a bent M-shape.

name: Hartlaub's Bustard
rangeDescription: Eastern sudan to ethiopia, somalia, northeastern uganda, and northern tanzania
description: A medium-sized, long-legged, long-necked bustard. The male has a striking black face pattern and a black line down the neck that connects to the black belly.

name: Iquitos Gnatcatcher
rangeDescription: White-sand forest in iquitos region (northeastern peru)
description: Rare bird known only from the Allpahuayo-Mishana National Reserve in the lowlands of northeastern Peru. Like other gnatcatchers, it is mainly gray and white; tail is black with white outer feathers.

name: Empress Brilliant
rangeDescription: Pacific slope of southwestern colombia to northwestern ecuador
description: Impressive hummingbird of Andean cloud forest in northwestern Ecuador and western Colombia. Large, thick-billed, and long-tailed, with golden sheen on the belly.

name: Yellow-collared Lovebird
rangeDescription: Tanzania
description: A colorful lovebird of East African savanna that is also found in woodland, cultivated areas, and around human habitation. Note the green back, the broad yellow collar, the black face, and the red bill.

name: Slender Antbird
rangeDescription: Highlands of eastern brazil (southeastern bahia and northeastern minas gerais)
description: Large, long-tailed antbird. Males are gray, paler below, with a black bib.

name: Tapajos Hermit
rangeDescription: Central amazonian brazil, east of the rio tapajós and rio teles peres
description: Tiny rufous hummingbird with a curved bill and a yellow lower mandible. Note the prominent white bases to the outer tail feathers.

name: Hooded Gnateater
rangeDescription: Northeastern brazil (eastern pará to western ceará and southern piauí)
description: Chunky little bird with long legs. Males have a black head and breast, while females have a rusty-brown head, white throat, and light gray underparts.

name: Angola Cave-Chat
rangeDescription: Rocky caves and gorges of western angola
description: Long-tailed, black-and-white chat. Note the mostly white outer tail.

name: Hodgson's Hawk-Cuckoo
rangeDescription: Breeds eastern nepal through eastern himalayas and indian hills south of the brahmaputra river to southern and eastern china, from southern sichuan northeastward to jiangsu and southeastward to hainan, and northern southeastern asia; winters to greater sundas
description: Large hawk-like cuckoo of dense forests, where it usually forages deep in the canopy. Adult gray above and pale below, with gray and orange blotches and loose streaks on breast.

name: White-breasted Cuckooshrike
rangeDescription: Brachystegia woodland of sub-saharan africa
description: Large, chunky, gray cuckooshrike with white underparts. There is a pale ring around the dark eye, giving the face a gentle appearance.

name: Gilbert's Honeyeater
rangeDescription: Southwestern western australia
description: Small honeyeater of eucalypt forests of southwestern Australia. Light olive above, whitish below, with black head broken by white band behind the eye and narrow white arc above it.

name: Upland Sandpiper
rangeDescription: Breeds alaska to southern usa; winters in south america
description: Distinctive sandpiper found in areas with short grass. Frequently seen perched on fence posts or atop small shrubs.

name: Red-knobbed Coot
rangeDescription: Southern spain and morocco; eastern and southern africa and madagascar
description: Mostly sooty gray waterbird with a white beak and frontal shield. Breeding adults have two small reddish horns, but at other times difficult to separate from Eurasian Coot.

name: Makira Leaf Warbler
rangeDescription: Makira (southeastern solomon islands)
description: A tiny warbler with a mostly gray head, a dark eye-stripe, and a pale eyebrow. Back and wings strongly green-toned with two buff wingbars.

name: Drab Seedeater
rangeDescription: Arid southern ecuador; upper marañón valley of northern peru southward to ica
description: Well-named seedeater found in arid scrub and adjacent farmland in western Peru and southwestern Ecuador. Its best field marks are the distinct wingbars and bill color (pinkish on breeding males, nearly black on other individuals).

name: Brazilian Merganser
rangeDescription: South-central south america (paraguai-paraná drainage system)
description: Unmistakable in range. Odd-looking duck with a long thin bill, dark green head, and spiky crest.

name: Northern Brownbul
rangeDescription: Southwestern sudan; southeastern south sudan, southern ethiopia, and southern somalia to northern uganda, kenya, and northeastern tanzania
description: A drab, long-tailed brownish bird related to greenbuls. The tail is rufous and the throat paler buff.

name: Long-tailed Woodnymph
rangeDescription: Coastal eastern brazil (eastern pará to pernambuco and bahia)
description: Fairly large, slim hummingbird with a slightly forked tail and straight bill. Males have iridescent green and violet-blue plumage and females are green above and white below.
